  "prompt": "What song was playing when the characters walked into the club to get their daughter in the movie \"Vegas Vacation\"?",
  "response": "In the movie **\"Vegas Vacation\"** (1997), the scene where the Griswold family enters a nightclub to find their daughter Audrey features the song **\"Get Ready\"** by **The Temptations**. This classic Motown track sets the tone for the family's comedic and heartfelt adventure in Las Vegas as they navigate various challenges to reunite with Audrey.\n\n**Song Details:**\n- **Title:** Get Ready\n- **Artist:** The Temptations\n- **Album:** Gettin' Ready\n- **Release Year:** 1966\n\n\"Get Ready\" is known for its smooth vocals and upbeat rhythm, making it a fitting choice for the vibrant and lively atmosphere of the nightclub scene in the film.",
